excerpt: A 230m-high observation deck & cafe offering sweeping Gold Coast views, plus nightlife on weekends.
detail_description: Located on the 77th and 78th levels of the Q1 building, SkyPoint Observation Deck offers breathtaking panoramic views of the Gold Coast and its hinterland. As Australia's only beachside observation deck, it stands at a remarkable height of 230 meters. Visitors can take in the stunning scenery through high-power binoculars and visual displays that highlight key points of interest in the region.
name: SkyPoint Observation Deck
address: Q1 Building, Level 77/9 Hamilton Ave, Surfers Paradise QLD 4217, Australia

excerpt: Sprawling amusement complex featuring themed areas, with rides, attractions & a wildlife park.
detail_description: Dreamworld is a massive amusement complex on the Gold Coast, offering a wide range of attractions and activities. It boasts the biggest and most thrilling rides in Australia, as well as a wildlife sanctuary and even the Big Brother House. With over 30 rides catering to all ages and preferences, there's something for everyone here. Visitors can enjoy experiences like Tiger Island, where majestic White Tigers roam freely, or catch some waves at Flow Rider.
name: Dreamworld

excerpt: Native animals on display in natural surrounds, plus shows, encounters & a wildlife hospital.
detail_description: Currumbin Wildlife Sanctuary is a popular Australian wildlife adventure located on over 25 hectares of natural eucalypt and rainforest. The sanctuary offers a chance to interact with native birds, marsupials, and reptiles, including hand-feeding wild lorikeets and kangaroos. Visitors can also walk a wombat, meet a dingo, or cuddle a koala.
name: Currumbin Wildlife Sanctuary

excerpt: Surfers Paradise is a seaside resort on Queensland's Gold Coast in eastern Australia. It's known for its high-rise skyline and Surfers Paradise Beach, which hosts a popular market several evenings a week. Along Cavill Avenue are shops, cafes and lively nightclubs. The towering Q1 building, with its SkyPoint observation deck, offers panoramic ocean and city views.
detail_description: Surfers Paradise is a vibrant seaside resort located on the Gold Coast in eastern Australia. The area boasts a striking high-rise skyline and is famous for its beautiful Surfers Paradise Beach, where a popular market takes place several evenings each week. Along Cavill Avenue, visitors can explore an array of shops, cafes, and lively nightclubs. One of the prominent landmarks in Surfers Paradise is the Q1 building, which features the SkyPoint observation deck offering breathtaking panoramic views of the ocean and city.
name: Surfers Paradise

excerpt: Huge park with walking tracks & campsites featuring rainforest, a natural bridge & waterfalls.
detail_description: Springbrook National Park is a vast expanse of natural beauty, offering visitors an immersive experience in the Queensland hinterland. Spanning over 20 square miles, this park is a haven for hikers and nature enthusiasts, boasting lush rainforests, serene walking tracks, and well-equipped campsites. The park's highlights include the stunning Natural Bridge and the majestic Purling Brook Falls, a breathtaking 100-meter waterfall that leaves an indelible impression on all who behold it.
name: Springbrook National Park

excerpt: Film-themed amusement park with thrill rides including rollercoasters & regular live stunt shows.
detail_description: Warner Bros. Movie World is a film-themed amusement park that offers an exhilarating experience for visitors of all ages. The park features thrilling rides, including the DC Rivals HyperCoaster, as well as live stunt shows such as the Hollywood Stunt Driver show. Families can meet their favorite characters from movies and cartoons, with opportunities to interact with superheroes and stars during daily parades.
name: Warner Bros. Movie World

excerpt: Unfussy indoor & outdoor night market with live music offering global street fare, cocktails & beer.
detail_description: Miami Marketta is a vibrant night market located in Miami's creative precinct, offering a diverse range of global street food, cocktails, and beer. Housed in a former mechanics warehouse, this iconic local gem hosts an array of street food vendors three times a week, filling the air with enticing aromas. With live music performances by local and international musicians, along with stand-up comedy and games, Miami Marketta provides unforgettable nights for visitors.
name: Miami Marketta

excerpt: Untouched rainforest park criss-crossed with walking trails and home to rare animals and birds.
detail_description: Lamington National Park is a stunning, untouched rainforest area that forms part of the Gondwana Rainforests of Australia World Heritage Area. It boasts a lush, subtropical-temperate zone with diverse plant and animal life, including rare species. The park features ancient Antarctic beech trees, picturesque waterfalls, mountain pools, vibrant wildflowers, and over 160 native bird species.
name: Lamington National Park

excerpt: Oceanographic theme park with marine animals & polar bears, plus shows, rides & interactive tours.
detail_description: Sea World is an oceanographic theme park that offers a variety of attractions for visitors of all ages. Guests can watch polar bears at Polar Bear Shores, observe tropical fish and sharks in the world's largest man-made shark lagoon, and even touch rays at Ray Reef. The park also features entertaining seal presentations and live dolphin shows.
name: Sea World
address: Seaworld Dr, Main Beach QLD 4217, Australia

excerpt: Burleigh Heads is a coastal suburb in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia. In the 2021 census, Burleigh Heads had a population of 10,572 people. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Burleigh Heads, located in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia, is a charming suburb with a population of over 10,000 people. This coastal gem offers an array of attractions and activities for visitors to enjoy. One notable establishment is Rosellas, a popular bar known for its Australian-themed ambiance and menu featuring locally sourced ingredients. The bar's creative cocktails and delectable toasties make it a beloved spot among locals and tourists alike.
name: Burleigh Heads

excerpt: Part of the Dreamworld amusement complex, this water park has slides, a wave pool & private cabanas.
detail_description: WhiteWater World is a thrilling water park located next to Dreamworld in the Gold Coast. It offers an array of exciting attractions, including adrenaline-pumping rides like the Green Room and The Rip for thrill-seekers, as well as more relaxed family-friendly slides and splash areas for little ones. With 12 slides to choose from, visitors can experience twists, turns, and exhilarating drops. For those seeking ultimate relaxation, luxury cabanas equipped with amenities are available.
name: WhiteWater World

excerpt: Bush-themed dinner show in a high-tech arena with horseback riding, cattle mustering & music.
detail_description: Australian Outback Spectacular is a captivating bush-themed dinner show set in a high-tech arena that offers an immersive experience into the heartland of Australia. The show follows the story of struggling farmers Reg and Marge, showcasing the challenges and resilience of outback life. Guests are treated to a three-course meal supporting local farmers while being entertained by horseback riding, cattle mustering, music, and impressive special effects.
name: Australian Outback Spectacular

excerpt: Intimate animal park with crocs, wallabies & many other native species, plus shows & feedings.
detail_description: David Fleay Wildlife Park, nestled in the tranquil Burleigh Heads area of the Gold Coast, is a charming destination for wildlife enthusiasts. Established by renowned naturalist David Fleay in 1952, this heritage park emphasizes animal conservation and creating natural habitats. Visitors can explore lush rainforests and wetlands while observing an impressive variety of native species such as crocodiles, wallabies, koalas, and even the elusive platypus named Wally.
name: David Fleay Wildlife Park
address: Loman Lane, Burleigh Heads QLD 4220, Australia

excerpt: Coastal headland area with shoreline & rainforest trails, plus wildlife viewing.
detail_description: Burleigh Head National Park is a surprising gem in Burleigh Heads, offering stunning ocean views, rainforest trails, and wildlife encounters. The coastal headland area provides an easy escape into nature with its rocky foreshore, ancient volcanic columns, and lush mangroves. Visitors can enjoy picnics or barbecues amidst fragrant pine trees while spotting whales during spring. The park features well-maintained walking tracks for exploring the diverse landscapes and relaxing by the ocean.
name: Burleigh Head National Park
address: Goodwin Terrace, Burleigh Heads QLD 4220, Australia

excerpt: Legendary surfing spot with a sand beach, set against a city backdrop with entertainment & shops.
detail_description: Surfers Paradise Beach is a legendary surfing spot located on the Gold Coast, offering a beautiful sandy beach against the backdrop of a vibrant city with entertainment and shops. While it may not offer the best surfing conditions compared to other nearby alternatives, its proximity to main attractions, theme parks, accommodations, nightlife, and entertainment make it incredibly popular and crowded year-round. The beach's convenient location near numerous restaurants, shopping outlets, and resorts compensates for its lack of big waves.
name: Surfers Paradise Beach

excerpt: Broadbeach is a suburb in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia. In the 2021 census, Broadbeach had a population of 6,786 people. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Broadbeach, located in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia, is a vibrant suburb with a population of around 6,786 people. Situated within the Gold Coast Central area, it is surrounded by other popular neighborhoods such as Surfers Paradise and Burleigh Heads. This coastal destination offers a mix of urban amenities and natural beauty, making it an attractive location for visitors and residents alike.
name: Broadbeach

excerpt: Popular stretch of white-sand beach with surf, scenic views & lifeguards on duty.
detail_description: Coolangatta Beach is a popular destination known for its stunning white-sand stretch, perfect waves for surfing, and breathtaking views. This area boasts two main beaches - Greenmount Beach and Rainbow Bay - both facing north, providing calm waters ideal for swimming. A short walk to Snapper Rocks increases the chance of spotting migrating whales during the cooler months. Coolangatta offers easy access to family attractions as well as the natural beauty of Northern NSW and the Tweed Valley.
name: Coolangatta Beach

excerpt: Natural formation with a unique rock pool along with scenic views overlooking the beach.
detail_description: Nestled at the southern tip of Queensland's coastline, Snapper Rocks is a stunning natural formation that boasts breathtaking views and a unique rock pool. Renowned for its world-famous surf break known as the Superbank, this location offers surfers some of the longest and hollowest waves on Earth. It's not just a favorite haunt for surfing legends like Mick Fanning; it also hosts prestigious competitions such as the annual World Surf Leagueâ€™s Quicksilver and Roxy Pros.
name: Snapper Rocks
address: Snapper Rocks Rd, Coolangatta QLD 4225, Australia

excerpt: Museum with kitschy oddities on display, including shrunken human heads & rare animal skeletons.
detail_description: Ripley's Believe It or Not! Surfers Paradise is a popular museum showcasing over 300 exhibits of bizarre oddities and rare artifacts. Visitors can marvel at shrunken human heads, unusual animal skeletons, and interactive displays that cater to all ages. The themed galleries feature unbelievable stories, illusions, and interactive games, while the 7D Moving Theatre offers an immersive motion simulator experience.
name: Ripley's Believe It or Not!
address: Cavill Ave, Surfers Paradise QLD 4217, Australia

excerpt: Coolangatta is a coastal suburb in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia. It is the Gold Coast's southernmost suburb and it borders New South Wales. In the 2021 census, Coolangatta had a population of 6,491 people. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Coolangatta, located in the City of Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia, is a charming coastal suburb that sits at the southernmost tip of the Gold Coast. With a population of around 5,948 people, this area offers stunning views from Mick Schamburg Park Lookout. From here, visitors can take in panoramic vistas that stretch from Surfers Paradise to Coolangatta Beach and beyond to Greenmount Beach, Snapper Rocks and Rainbow Bay Beach.
name: Coolangatta
